def explore_video(file_path):
    sucess = True
    explorer = {
        'equal_channels': True,
        'diff_frames': [],
        'shape': None,
        'qtd_frames': 0,
        'sample': None
    }

    cap = cv2.VideoCapture(file_path)
    while True:
        sucess, frame = cap.read()
        if sucess == False:
            break

        explorer['qtd_frames'] += 1
        if explorer['shape'] is None:
            explorer['shape'] = frame.shape
            explorer['sample'] = frame
        explorer['equal_channels'] = explorer['equal_channels'] and \
            (frame[:,:,0] == frame[:,:,1]).all() and (frame[:,:,0] == frame[:,:,2]).all()
        if ((frame[:,:,0] == frame[:,:,1]).all() and (frame[:,:,0] == frame[:,:,2]).all()) == False:
            explorer['diff_frames'].append(frame)
    cap.release()

    print('Name:', file_path)
    print("qtd_frames:", explorer['qtd_frames'])
    print("shape:", explorer['shape'])
    print("equal channels:", explorer['equal_channels'])
    print('Qtd. diff frames:', len(explorer['diff_frames']))

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()

    ax.imshow(explorer['sample'], # [:,:,0]
            #   cmap="jet",
            )
    ax.set_title(file_path.split(os.sep)[-1])
    ax.set_axis_off()
    plt.show()

    print('=' * 30, '\n')

    return explorer

from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.colors as mcolors
from scipy.interpolate import interp1d
from scipy.io import loadmat, savemat
from scipy import stats
import heartpy as hp
import numpy as np
import natsort
import logging

#Set colorblind mode
hp.config.colorblind = True
hp.config.colorblind_type = 'deuteranopia'
#change palette
hp.config.color_style = 'zesty'

def plot_measure_bars(measures_dict: dict, use_measures: list, title: str, fig_size: tuple = (20, 10), show=True):
    plt.figure(figsize=fig_size)
    color = list(mcolors.BASE_COLORS.keys()) + list(mcolors.TABLEAU_COLORS.keys())
    color.remove('w')
    # para cada measures_dict: 
    # key: nome do sujeito
    # value: dicionario de medidas
    for i, (key, value) in enumerate(measures_dict.items()):
        # para medida que o usuario quer mostrar
        medidas = {nome: measure for nome, measure in value.items() if nome in use_measures}

        positions = np.array(range(len(medidas)))
        width = 0.5 / len(measures_dict)

        plt.bar(
            x=positions + ((i/2)/len(measures_dict)), 
            height=medidas.values(), 
            label=key, 
            color=color[i], 
            width=width
        )

    plt.xticks(positions + width, medidas.keys())
    plt.title(title)
    plt.ylabel('Valor da medida')
    plt.xlabel('Medidas (heartpy)')
    plt.legend()
    if show:
        plt.show()
    else:
        return plt

def interpolate_grow(bpm, step):
    bpm = np.array(bpm)
    
    assert np.isnan(bpm).any() == False, "O array BPM nao deve conter NaN, use a funcao interpolate_nan antes dessa"

    # create x for each position:
    # x = array([4, 8, 12, 16, 20, ...])
    # len(x) igual a len(measures)
    x = np.arange(start=step, stop=len(bpm)*step+1, step=step)

    interp = interp1d(x, bpm, kind='linear', bounds_error=False)

    # aplica a interpolacao no range que tem quatro vezes o tamanho da variavel measures
    # array(0, 1, 2, 3, ...)
    bpm = interp(np.arange(start=step, stop=len(bpm)*step+1))
    
    return bpm

def interpolate_outliers(bpm, step):
    # codigo baseado no zscore do site: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/detect-and-remove-the-outliers-using-python/
    bpm = np.array(bpm)
    
    assert np.isnan(bpm).any() == False, "O array BPM nao deve conter NaN, use a funcao interpolate_nan antes dessa"
    
    z = np.abs(stats.zscore(bpm))

    # Fill zero on the position of the outlier
    # bpm[np.where(z > 4)[0]] = 0

    x = np.arange(len(bpm))
    
    # Recolhe BPM sem outliers
    bpm_filtered = bpm[np.where(z < 3)[0]]
    x = x[np.where(z < 3)[0]]

    interp = interp1d(x, bpm_filtered, kind='linear', bounds_error=False)

    # aplica a interpolacao no range com o tamanho total da variavel measures
    bpm = interp(np.arange(len(bpm)))
    
    return bpm

def interpolate_nan(bpm):
    bpm = np.array(bpm)

    x = np.arange(len(bpm))

    if np.isnan(bpm[0]):
        bpm[0] = bpm[np.where(np.isnan(bpm) == False)[0]].mean()

    if np.isnan(bpm[-1]):
        bpm[-1] = bpm[np.where(np.isnan(bpm) == False)[0]].mean()

    # Recolhe BPM sem outliers
    bpm_filtered = bpm[np.where(np.isnan(bpm) == False)[0]]
    x = x[np.where(np.isnan(bpm) == False)[0]]

    interp = interp1d(x, bpm_filtered, kind='linear', bounds_error=False)

    # aplica a interpolacao no range com o tamanho total da variavel measures
    bpm = interp(np.arange(len(bpm)))
    
    return bpm

def explore_ppg(dataset_path: str):
    """
    # TODO adicionar descricao da funcao
    """
    # VERIFICACAO DAS PASTAS E ARQUIVOS BASE

    # pasta do dataset base tem que existir
    assert os.path.isdir(dataset_path), f"dataset_path nao eh um diretorio: {dataset_path}"

    ppg_paths = []

    # para cada pasta dentro do dataset base
    for subject_folder_name in os.listdir(dataset_path):
        subject_folder = os.path.join(dataset_path, subject_folder_name)

        # para assumir que a pasta subject_folder pode conter um sujeito temos que verificar:
        # se ela eh um diretorio
        # se ela contem a pasta 'PulseOX' e o arquivo 'pulseOx.mat' existe
        # se ela contem uma das seguintes pastas: RGB ou NIR
        if os.path.exists(os.path.join(subject_folder, 'pulseOx.mat')):
            ppg_paths.append((subject_folder_name, subject_folder, os.path.join(subject_folder, 'pulseOx.mat')))

    # ordena de forma 'natural' a lista de path
    ppg_paths = natsort.natsorted(ppg_paths)

    dataset_json = {}
    bpm_hist = {}

    # EXECUCAO DO GERADOR DOS RECORTES DE CADA VIDEO

    # para cada video que precisa ser processado
    for (subject_folder_name, subject_folder_path, ppg_path) in ppg_paths:
        try:
            mat = loadmat(ppg_path)
            ppg = mat['pulseOxRecord'][0]

            # ppg = np.concatenate([x.ravel() for x in pulse.ravel()])

            wd, m = hp.process(ppg, sample_rate = 60.0)

            pointcare = hp.plot_poincare(wd, m, show=False, figsize=(20, 10))
            pointcare.savefig(os.path.join(subject_folder_path, 'pointcare.png'))

            hp.plotter(wd, m, figsize=(20, 10))

            dataset_json[subject_folder_name] = m

            wd, m = hp.process_segmentwise(ppg, sample_rate = 60.0, segment_width=4, segment_overlap=0.75)

            m['bpm'] = interpolate_nan(m['bpm'])
            m['bpm'] = interpolate_outliers(m['bpm'], step=1)
            
            plt.plot(np.arange(start=4, stop=len(m['bpm'])+4), m['bpm'], color='r', label=f'Frequência cardíaca - Step: 1')
            #x=np.arange(start=4, stop=len(m['bpm'])+4, step=1)
            
            wd, m = hp.process_segmentwise(ppg, sample_rate = 60.0, segment_width=4)
            
            m['bpm'] = interpolate_nan(m['bpm'])
            m['bpm'] = interpolate_grow(m['bpm'], step=4)
            m['bpm'] = interpolate_outliers(m['bpm'], step=4)
            
            plt.plot(np.arange(start=4, stop=len(m['bpm'])+4), m['bpm'], color='b', label=f'Frequência cardíaca - Step: 4')
            #x=np.arange(start=4, stop=len(m['bpm'])*4+1, step=4)

            bpm_hist[subject_folder_name] = m['bpm']

            # 1234 5678 ...
            # 1234 2345 3456 ...
            
            plt.title(f'Picos dos pulsos do PPG e os batimentos por minuto - {subject_folder_name}')
            plt.ylabel('Beats per minute (BPM)')
            plt.xlabel('Tempo (segundos)')
            plt.legend()
            # plt.show()
            plt.savefig(os.path.join(subject_folder_path, 'ppg_hr_graph.png'))
            # TODO salvar no arquivo matlab os batimentos em cada segundo (deve conter quatro segundos a menos que o PPG)
            # TODO salvar plots de momentos que o PPG esta com campos multivalorados

            mat['bpm'] = m['bpm']
            savemat(os.path.join(subject_folder_path, 'pulseOx_bpm.mat'), mat)
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"Exception nao mapeada: \n{logging.traceback.format_exc()}")
            pass

    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))

    for subject, bpms in bpm_hist.items():
        plt.hist(bpms, label=subject, alpha=0.5)

    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Histograma da distribuição de batimentos de cada sujeito')
    # plt.show()
    plt.ylabel('Frequência')
    plt.xlabel('Beats per minute (BPM)')
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(dataset_path, 'bpm_histogram.png'))

    bar = plot_measure_bars(measures_dict=dataset_json, use_measures=['bpm', 'sdnn', 'sdsd', 'mssd', 'hr_mad', 'sd1', 'sd2'], title='Medidas Time-domain', show=False)
    bar.savefig(os.path.join(dataset_path, 'measures_1.png'))
    
    # plot_measure_bars(measures_dict=dataset_json, use_measures=['s'], title='COLOCAR TITULO')
    bar = plot_measure_bars(measures_dict=dataset_json, use_measures=['ibi'], title='Intervalo médio entre batimentos', show=False)
    plt.ylabel('Intervalo entre batimentos (milisegundos)')
    bar.savefig(os.path.join(dataset_path, 'measures_2.png'))

    bar = plot_measure_bars(measures_dict=dataset_json, use_measures=['pnn20', 'pnn50', 'sd1/sd2', 'breathingrate'], title='Medidas Time-domain', show=False)
    bar.savefig(os.path.join(dataset_path, 'measures_3.png'))

    bpm = np.array(bpm)
    bpm = np.nan_to_num(bpm, nan=0)

    # array(0, 1, 2, 3, ...)
    bpm = interp(np.arange(start=step, stop=len(bpm)*step+1))
    
    return bpm

from typing import Union, List, Tuple
def heart_rate(
    x: Union[List, np.ndarray], sfreq: int = 1000, unit: str = "rr", kind: str = "cubic"
) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:
    """Transform peaks data into heart rate time series.
    Parameters
    ----------
    x : np.ndarray or list
        Boolean vector of peaks detection.
    sfreq : int
        Sampling frequency.
    unit : str
        The heartrate unit in use. Can be 'rr' (R-R intervals, in ms)
        or 'bpm' (beats per minutes). Default is 'rr'.
    kind : str
        The method to use (parameter of `scipy.interpolate.interp1d`).
    Returns
    -------
    heartrate : np.ndarray
        The heart rate frequency.
    time : np.ndarray
        Time array.
    Notes
    -----
    The input should be in the form of a boolean vector encoding the position
    of the peaks. The time and heart rate output will have the same
    length. Values before the first peak and after the last peak will be filled
    with NaN values.
    """
    if isinstance(x, list):
        x = np.asarray(x)
    if not ((x == 1) | (x == 0)).all():
        raise ValueError("Input vector should only contain 0 and 1")

    # Find peak indices
    peaks_idx = np.where(x)[0]

    # Create time vector (seconds):
    time = (peaks_idx / sfreq)[1:]

    rr = np.diff(peaks_idx)

    # R-R heartratevals (in miliseconds)
    heartrate = (rr / sfreq) * 1000
    if unit == "bpm":
        # Beats per minutes
        heartrate = 60000 / heartrate

    # Use the peaks vector as time input
    new_time = np.arange(0, len(x) / sfreq, 1 / sfreq)

    if kind is not None:
        # Interpolate
        f = interp1d(
            time, heartrate, kind=kind, bounds_error=False, fill_value=(np.nan, np.nan)
        )
        heartrate = f(new_time)

    return heartrate, new_time
